NAME
    gcloud alpha spanner operations describe - describe a Cloud Spanner
        operation

SYNOPSIS
    gcloud alpha spanner operations describe OPERATION-ID --instance=INSTANCE
        [--database=DATABASE] [GCLOUD_WIDE_FLAG ...]

DESCRIPTION
    (ALPHA) Describe a Cloud Spanner operation.

POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS
     OPERATION-ID
        ID of the operation

REQUIRED FLAGS
     --instance=INSTANCE
        The ID of the instance the operation is executing on.

OPTIONAL FLAGS
     --database=DATABASE
        For a database operation, the name of the database the operation is
        executing on.

GCLOUD WIDE FLAGS
    These flags are available to all commands: --account, --configuration,
    --flatten, --format, --help, --log-http, --project, --quiet, --trace-token,
    --user-output-enabled, --verbosity. Run $ gcloud help for details.

NOTES
    This command is currently in ALPHA and may change without notice. If this
    command fails with API permission errors despite specifying the right
    project, you will have to apply for early access and have your projects
    registered on the API whitelist to use it. To do so, contact Support at
    https://cloud.google.com/support/. These variants are also available:

        $ gcloud spanner operations describe
        $ gcloud beta spanner operations describe

